Show HN: An unofficial web app to explore GitHub's top repositories
text:
I don't always explore the top GitHub repositories but when I do, it's a bad experience because:

- I have to keep switching pages.

- Many of the repos shown are repos that I'm not interested in but have no choice except to scroll through them every time.

The app shows all the top 1000 repos on one page and you can blacklist the repos you're not interested in so whenever you go back you don't have to scroll through them.

Related: https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=9413590
